description.html:
Daktronics Expectations as of 03/13/2024: 

  1. Accept or decline new WO’s via the FN platform for stores within your area that you plan to action within 1-business day of the WO routed date.
  2. Execute accepted WO’s within 3-business days from the accepted date.
  3. If parts are in transit, execute accepted WO's within 3-business days from the part(s) delivery date.


**********************************************************************************************


Reminder: Please do not dispatch during the lunch rush between 11AM-1PM


﻿Please call the store to confirm they are open before going onsite

Please perform Service Monday - Friday (No Weekends)


Could you please dispatch a tech to troubleshoot and/or replace (if necessary) [Equipment] at the location indicated. 


[Additional Notes or Instructions Section]

%description.html%

Dress Code

Please introduce yourself as representing Adflow Networks.

Buttoned shirt, Company Branded Polo and khakis

No jeans 


Scope of work:

  1. Ask to speak to the person running shift
  2. Work with ADFLOW to get player online to customer network
  3. Confirm the new player is online to our end
  4. Test and confirm content with Adflow
  5. Test and confirm ScreenControl with Adflow
  6. Send the final pictures for the service call before receiving the exit code


*Sample Pictures attached to illustrate what we require


 Confirming the screen order and content before leaving the site is mandatory as part of the service call.



Tools Required: 

  • Wireless USB keyboard & mouse
  • Monitor that supports HDMI input at 1920x1080
  • Laptop that support HDMI input at 1920x1080
  • Smartphone/camera with emailing capabilities
  • Standard size 8ft ladder
  • Label Maker
  • Standard tool kit - Screw drivers, cable cutters, drill, etc.

  

ADFLOW Contact: Upon arrival please call into Adflow Support at 1-800-325-8766. Options: 2, *, 1, 9
